  "security_observations": {
    "identity_axes": "The simulated verified-A carrier remains forwarding-only and must differ from the manifest-enrolled Ed25519 signer at both principal and entity identity. The immutable handoff retains both identities, carrier role/profile, stable-core digest, security-state digest, and exact signed payload bytes.",
    "envelope_profile": "The outer object is exactly flattened JWS protected/payload/signature with canonical unpadded base64url, literal Ed25519 algorithm and prototype type, crit=[ncp], no unprotected or remote key material, exact received encoded signing input, and a content-addressed current manifest key.",
    "ncp_binding": "The signed context separates forwarding epoch/sequence and recovery epoch from canonical UUIDv4 NCP session generation, conditional stream position, and conditional operation id/request digest/expected state version. Full NCP session, lease, idempotency, lifecycle, safety, and plant admission remain downstream.",
    "replay": "Replay uses an owner-only SQLite store, exact schema SQL, WAL plus synchronous FULL, BEGIN IMMEDIATE conditional high-water upsert, commit-before-handoff, bounded replay scopes, bounded main and sidecar files, and public API replay-key validation. Equal or lower sequences and every storage error reject.",
    "recovery": "Initialization requires an absent path. Owner-signed recovery must advance by exactly one recovery epoch to a distinct store ID; the signed envelope recovery epoch fences every old envelope. A cooperative shared/exclusive advisory lock prevents replacement while another conforming local process is active.",
    "known_limits": "Commit-before-handoff is honest at-most-once and can lose a handoff after commit. Filesystem snapshot rollback is not detected without an external monotonic anchor. Non-cooperating same-UID processes, shared filesystems, replicated state, owner-key custody, trusted time, disk-full, kill-during-COMMIT, WAL-aware backup/restore, duration fuzz, soak, performance, live composition with prototype A, and independent parser agreement are unproved."
  },
